-- Cemex Falls Most in Three Months in Mexico City Trading
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-02-24T21:44:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-24/cemex-falls-most-in-three-months-in-mexico-city-trading.html
Cemex (CEMEXCPO)  SAB, the largest cement maker
in the Americas, fell the most in three months.  Cemex shares dropped 6.7 percent to 9.45 pesos today in
Mexico City, the most since Nov. 23. The benchmark IPC index of
35 Mexican stocks slipped 0.2 percent.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
